by nicolas-grekas at 2015-06-16T12:22:32Z

Fatal errors on HHVM use the 16777217 magic number.
But since `16777217 == E_ERROR + 0x1000000;` the only required tweak is to remove this leading `1`.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

by staabm at 2015-06-17T19:03:38Z

Feels like this should be reported as a php incompatibility to hhvm

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

by nicolas-grekas at 2015-06-18T09:39:56Z

I took some time to test the Debug component on HHVM.

The main differences are:
- the 6th $backtrace argument
- the hhvm.error_handling.call_user_handler_on_fatals=1 behavior
- the `16777217 == E_ERROR + 0x1000000` special error level

This PR handles all of them and gives full HHVM support to the component.
Ping @symfony/deciders

